The Medi­ter­ra­nean is a sea that has expe­ri­enced extra­or­di­nary contacts, conf­licts, enco­un­ters and exchanges through the centu­ries. This comple­xity is analysed in the present volume through the eyes of twelve scho­lars specia­lised in Middle Eastern and North African studies. Arabic and Semitic lingu­istics and dialec­to­logy, Arab lite­ra­ture and popular music and culture are some of the broad range of subjects included in this volume which engages diffe­rent geogra­phical areas of the so-called Mare Nostrum and various histo­rical periods, from the medieval to the contem­porary era.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aAvallone, Lucia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaba, Ahmed-Salem Ould Mohamed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassuto, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Blasio, Emanuela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Anna, Luca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiranescu, Daniela Rodica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorvat, Bohdan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalach, Najla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLa Spisa, Paolo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMansour, Jihène Jerbi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMion, Giuliano, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRosenbaum, Gabriel M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVentura, Annamaria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08